                <head>269. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>At a luncheon on March 21, President <persName corresp="#p_EDD1"
                        >Eisenhower</persName>’s guests were Prime Minister <persName
                        corresp="#p_MH1">Macmillan</persName>, Foreign Secretary <persName
                        corresp="#p_LSJSB1">Lloyd</persName>, Secretary of State <persName
                        corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName>, the President’s Staff Secretary General
                        <persName corresp="#p_GCAJ1">Goodpaster</persName>, and <persName
                        corresp="#p_DPH1">Patrick Dean</persName>, Deputy Under Secretary at the
                    Foreign Office. (Eisenhower Library, President’s Appointment Book)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
